cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Trajectory Geometry: Measuring the Shape of Reasoning in Transformers"
authors:
  - family-names: Soliman
    given-names: Kareem
type: software
date-released: 2026-03-09
url: "https://github.com/solimankareem159-glitch/Trajectory-Geometry"
repository-code: "https://github.com/solimankareem159-glitch/Trajectory-Geometry"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - mechanistic interpretability
  - transformer reasoning
  - trajectory geometry
  - hidden state dynamics
  - chain-of-thought
  - geometric signatures
  - dimensional collapse
abstract: >-
  When a transformer model reasons correctly, its hidden states trace
  geometrically distinct trajectories compared to when it fails. This
  repository documents 19 experiments discovering, validating, and
  stress-testing geometric signatures of reasoning across multiple
  model architectures (Qwen, Pythia) and scales (70M to 3B parameters).
  Key findings include dimensional collapse in failure (Cohen's d > 4.5),
  regime-relative success signatures, difficulty-driven geometric expansion
  (d > 17.0), and architecture-invariant commitment dynamics.
